==Dutch==

===Pronunciation===

* ['vrɛiən]

===Intransitive verb===
'''vrijen''' (''[[past tense]]'' '''[[vrijde]]/[[vrijden]]''' ''[[past participle]]'' '''[[gevrijd]]''')

# To make love, to have sex, to get laid.
#: ''Het is heel belangrijk om veilig te vrijen.'' (It's very important to have safe sex)
# To make out, to cuddle, to hug and kiss.
#: ''Zij vroeg haar vriendje om eerst gewoon te vrijen.'' (She asked her boyfriend to just kiss and hug first)
# To have a relationship, to be a couple, to go out with someone.
#: ''Zij heeft haar vriend Alex leren kennen op Internet en ze vrijen al meer dan een jaar nu.'' (She met her boyfriend Alex in Internet and now they go out together for more than a year already)

